        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def send_alert(message: str, severity: str, webhook_url: str) -> None:\n    import urllib.request, json as _json\n    payload = _json.dumps({\"text\": f\"[{severity}] Continuous Eval Alert: {message}\"}).encode()\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        webhook_url,\n        data=payload,\n        headers={\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n        method=\"POST\",\n    )\n    urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5)\n\ndef run_pipeline(conn, monitors: dict, webhook_url: str) -> None:\n    sample = sampler.drain()\n    if not sample:\n        return\n    graded = asyncio.run(grade_batch(sample))\n    store_batch(conn, graded, version=\"v1.0\")\n\n    mean_score = sum(r[\"score\"] for r in graded if r.get(\"score\")) / len(graded)\n\n    ewma_result = monitors[\"ewma\"].update(mean_score)\n    cusum_result = monitors[\"cusum\"].update(mean_score)\n\n    if cusum_result[\"alert\"]:\n        send_alert(f\"CUSUM alert: S={cusum_result['S']}, score={mean_score:.2f}\", \"HIGH\", webhook_url)\n    elif ewma_result[\"alert\"]:\n        send_alert(f\"EWMA alert: ewma={ewma_result['ewma']}, floor={ewma_result['floor']}\", \"MEDIUM\", webhook_url)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using Pipeline Output to Grow the Eval Suite"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The continuous pipeline does double duty: it monitors quality and it harvests new test cases. Low-scoring samples from production are the highest-value additions to your offline eval suite \u2014 they represent real failures the suite did not anticipate."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def harvest_failures(\n    conn: sqlite3.Connection,\n    threshold: float = 2.5,\n    limit: int = 20,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Return recently low-scoring cases for human review and suite addition.\"\"\"\n    rows = conn.execute(\n        \"\"\"SELECT input_hash, score, timestamp\n           FROM scores\n           WHERE score <= ? AND timestamp > ?\n           ORDER BY score ASC\n           LIMIT ?\"\"\",\n        (threshold, time.time() - 86400 * 7, limit),\n    ).fetchall()\n    return [{\"input_hash\": r[0], \"score\": r[1], \"timestamp\": r[2]} for r in rows]\n\n# Review these cases, label correct outputs, add to suites/core.jsonl"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A continuous eval pipeline that feeds low-quality cases back into the offline suite creates a virtuous cycle: the suite grows from real failures, the offline eval becomes more predictive, and the continuous monitor has a better baseline to detect future regressions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Operational Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Grader cost. ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "LLM-based grading costs tokens. For high-traffic systems, sample 1-2% of requests and use a fast, cheap judge model. At 10,000 requests/day and 1% sampling, you grade 100 requests/day \u2014 manageable on claude-haiku-4-5-20251001."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Grader latency. ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run the grading job asynchronously, decoupled from the user-facing request path. A background worker that processes the last hour's samples is the standard pattern."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Baseline drift. ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "As you improve your prompt, the quality baseline rises. Update the EWMA floor and CUSUM target every 30-60 days to reflect the new normal \u2014 otherwise the detector will stop firing on regressions that would previously have triggered it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Privacy. ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Production samples may contain PII. Anonymize or redact before storing. Never send raw user inputs to a third-party eval service without a data processing agreement."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A continuous eval pipeline on production traffic samples is the quality monitoring layer that offline evals cannot provide. It runs daily or hourly, scoring a fraction of real requests and accumulating a time series that drift detectors watch for regression."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sample production traffic with reservoir sampling to get a representative, unbiased window"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
